A driver and passenger are lucky to be alive after the vehicle they had been travelling in crashed into the back of a small truck, along the R616 Bergville in the Action Homes area recently. Okhahlamba Search and Rescue volunteer officials and KwaZulu-Natal emergency Services (KZNEMS) told The Ladysmith Herald that the cause of  the accident was not known. “They had escaped with slight injuries and stabilised by KZNEMS before being taken to the local hospital for further medical treatment,” said officials on the scene.